\p  
\v 35 All \em these were\em* in holy serving; and the children of Solomon \em were\em* four hundred fourscore and two. 
\p  
\v 36 These be the sons that went up to \sls (or from)\sls* Thermeleth and Thelsas; the princes of them \em were\em* Charaathalar and Alar; 
\p  
\v 37 and they might not tell out their cities, and their progenies, what manner they be; and of Israel, the sons of Dalan, the sons of Ban, the sons of Necodan, \sls (six hundred and fifty-two)\sls*. 
\p  
\v 38 And of the priests, that used \sls (the office of the)\sls* priesthood, and were \add [not]\add* found; the sons of Obdia, the sons of Accos, the sons of Joddus, that took Augia \sls (as his)\sls* wife, \sls (one)\sls* of the daughters of Barzillai, and they be called by the name of her; 
\p  
\v 39 and of these is sought the genealogy written \add [or the written genealogy]\add* of the kindred, and they be prevented to use \sls (the office of the)\sls* priesthood. 
\p  
\v 40 And Nehemiah said to them, and Attharias, that they take not part of the holy things, till the time that there arise a taught bishop, into showing \sls (or revelation)\sls* and truth. 
\p  
\v 41 All Israel forsooth was twelve thousand \sls (or All Israel twelve years of age and older)\sls*, out-take \sls (or besides)\sls* servants and handmaidens, two and forty thousand three hundred and sixty. 
\p  
\v 42 The servants of \add [them, and]\add*\sls (the)\sls* handmaidens \em were\em* seven thousand three hundred and seven and thirty \sls (or forty)\sls*; singers and singsters \add [or singeresses]\add*, two hundred and five and sixty \sls (or forty)\sls*; 
\p  
\v 43 camels, four hundred and five and thirty; horses, seven thousand six and thirty; mules, two hundred thousand and five and forty \sls (or two hundred and five and forty)\sls*; beasts under yoke, five thousand \sls (and five hundred)\sls* and five and twenty. 
\p  
\v 44 And of those provosts, \em or reeves\em*, by towns, while they should come into the temple of God, that was in Jeru-salem, to be avowed to rear up the temple in his place, after their virtue; 
\p  
\v 45 and the holy treasury to be given into the temple of works \add [or to be given into the temple \+sls (into)\+sls* the holy treasury of works]\add*, \em were\em* eleven thousand bezants, and an hundred priests’ stoles. 
\p  
\v 46 And there dwelled \sls (the)\sls* priests, and deacons \add [or Levites]\add*, and \em others\em*, that were of the people, in Jerusalem, and in the realm \add [or region]\add*; and the holy singers, and ushers \sls (or the porters)\sls*, and all Israel, in their regions. 
\p  
\v 47 While the seventh month \em yet\em* lasted, and when the sons of Israel were each in his own things, they came together of one accord into the porch \sls (or open space)\sls*, that was before the east gate. 
\p  
\v 48 And while Jesus, \sls (or Jeshua, or Joshua)\sls*, the son of Josedek, and his brethren, \sls (the)\sls* priests, stood, and Zerubbabel, the son of Salathiel, and his brethren, they made ready an altar, 
\p  
\v 49 that they would offer on it burnt sacrifices, after those things that be written in the book of Moses, the man of God. 
\p  
\v 50 And there came to them of other nations of the land, and reared \sls (up)\sls* the holy treasury in his \sls (or its own)\sls* place, all the folk of the land; and they offered hosts, and burnt sacrifices of the morrowtide to the Lord. 
\p  
\v 51 And they did the feast of tabernacles, and a solemn day, as it is written in the law, and sacrifices each day, as it behooved. 
\p  
\v 52 And after these things they ordain-ed offerings, and hosts of sabbaths, and of new moons, and of all solemn days hallowed \add [or all hallowed solemn days]\add*. 
\p  
\v 53 And how many ever vowed to the Lord, from the \em time of the\em* new moon of the seventh month, they took hosts to offer to God; and the temple of the Lord was not yet builded up \add [or yet was not built up]\add*. 
\p  
\v 54 And they gave money to masons, and to wrights, and drinks \add [or and drink]\add* and meats, with joy. 
\p  
\v 55 And they gave cars \sls (or carts)\sls* to \sls (the)\sls* Sidonians and to \sls (the)\sls* Tyrians \sls (or the men of Tyre)\sls*, that they should carry over to them from Lebanon wood cedar beams, and to make a navy into the haven of Joppa, after the decree that was written to them from Cyrus, king of Persia. 
\p  
\v 56 And in the second year \sls (after)\sls* they came into \sls (or back to)\sls* the temple of God, into Jerusalem; the second month Zerubbabel began, the son of Salathiel, and Jesus, \sls (or Jeshua, or Joshua)\sls*, the son of Josedek, and the brethren of them, and \sls (the)\sls* priests, and Levites \sls (or deacons)\sls*, and all they that came from the captivity into Jerusalem; 
\p  
\v 57 and founded the temple of God, in the new moon of the second month of the second year, when they had come into Judea and to Jerusalem; 
\p  
\v 58 and set deacons \add [or Levites]\add* from \em the age of\em* twenty years \sls (old)\sls* upon the works of the Lord. And Jesus, \sls (or Jeshua, or Joshua)\sls*, stood, \sls (and)\sls* his son\sls (s)\sls*, and his brethren, all the deacons \add [or all Levites]\add* together casting, and executors, \em or followers\em*, of the law, and doing works in the house of the Lord. 
\p  
\v 59 And there stood \sls (the)\sls* priests, hav-ing stoles, \em or long clothes\em*, with trumps, and \sls (the)\sls* Levites \sls (or the deacons)\sls*, the sons of Asaph, having cymbals, 
\p  
\v 60 together praising the Lord, and blessing him, after \em the manner of\em* David, king of Israel. 
\p  
\v 61 And they sung a song to the Lord, for his sweetness and his worship into worlds, \em or ever \+sls (more)\+sls*\em*, upon all Israel. 
\p  
\v 62 And all the people sung with trumps, and cried with \sls (a)\sls* great \sls (or a loud)\sls* voice, praising together the Lord, in the rearing \sls (up)\sls* of the Lord’s house. 
\p  
\v 63 And there came \em many\em* of the priests, and of \sls (the)\sls* deacons \add [or Levites]\add*, and of \sls (the)\sls* presidents after \sls (the)\sls* towns \sls (or the princes of the towns)\sls*, to the elders that had seen the rather house \sls (or the first Temple)\sls*, and at the building up of this \em house\em*, with cry\sls (ing)\sls*, and with great wailing; 
\p  
\v 64 and many with trumps, and great joy, 
\p  
\v 65 so that the people heard not the trumps, for the great wailing of the people. Forsooth there was a company singing worshipfully in trumps \sls (or with the trumpets)\sls*, so that it was heard afar. 
\p  
\v 66 And the enemies heard the lineages of Judah and of Benjamin, and came to know, what was this voice \sls (or meaning)\sls* of \sls (the)\sls* trumps. 
\p  
\v 67 And they knew, that they that were of the captivity builded, \add [or built]\add*, the temple to the Lord God of Israel. 
\p  
\v 68 And \em the enemies\em* coming nigh to Zerubbabel, and to Jesus, \sls (or Jeshua, or Joshua)\sls*, and to the reeves of \sls (the)\sls* towns, they said to them, We shall build together with you. 
\p  
\v 69 In like manner forsooth we have heard our Lord, and we have gone together from the days of Asbasareth \sls (or Esarhaddon)\sls*, king of Assyrians, that over-passed from hence, \add [or that went over hence]\add*, \sls (or that brought us here)\sls*. 
\p  
\v 70 And Zerubbabel, and Jesus, \sls (or Jeshua, or Joshua)\sls*, and the princes of the towns of Israel said to them, It \sls (be)\sls*longeth not to us and to you \em together\em* to build up the house of our God; 
\p  
\v 71 forsooth we alone shall build the house of our God, after those things, that Cyrus, king of Persia, commanded. 
\p  
\v 72 The Gentiles forsooth of the land living with them that be in Judea, and rearing up the work of building, and bringing forth both \sls (their)\sls* espies and people, they prevented them to build up; 
\p  
\v 73 and they hindered \sls (the)\sls* men, haunting the goings-to, \sls (so)\sls* that the building should not be ended in all the time of the life of the king Cyrus; and they drew along the making-up by two years, unto the reign of Darius. 
\c 6  
\cl CHAPTER 6 
\p  
\v 1 Forsooth in the second year of the realm of Darius, Haggai prophesied, and Zechariah, the son of Addo, a prophet, with Judea and in Jerusalem, in the name of the Lord God of Israel, upon them. 
\p  
\v 2 Then standing Zerubbabel, the son of Salathiel, and Jesus, \sls (or Jeshua, or Joshua)\sls*, the son of Josedek, \em they\em* began to build up the house of the Lord, that is in Jerusalem; when there were nigh to them, \sls (yea)\sls*, \sls (the)\sls* prophets of the Lord, and helped them. 
\p  
\v 3 In that time came to them Sisinnes, the under-little-king of Syria and of Phenice \sls (or Phoenicia)\sls*, and Sathrabuzanes, and his fellows. And they said to them, 
\p  
\v 4 Who commanded to you, that ye build this house, and this roof, and many other things \sls (that)\sls* ye perform? and who be those builders \add [or the builders]\add*, that build up these things? 
\p  
\v 5 And the elder men of Israel had grace of \sls (or from)\sls* the Lord, when the visitation of them was made upon them that were of the captivity; 
\p  
\v 6 and they were not hindered to build up, to the time that it were signified to Darius of all these things, and an answer were taken \em again\em*. 
\p  
\v 7 \em This is\em* the ensample of the letter, that Sisinnes, the under-\sls (little-)\sls*king of Syria and of Phenice \sls (or of Phoenicia)\sls*, and Sathrabuzanes, and their fellows, rulers in Syria and in Phenice \sls (or in Phoenicia)\sls*, sent \em to the king\em*. To king Darius, greeting\sls (s)\sls*. 
\p  
\v 8 All things be they known to the lord the king; forsooth when we came into the region of Judea, and went into Jerusalem, we found men 
\p  
\v 9 building a great house of God, and a temple of great polished stones, and of precious materials in the walls; 
\p  
\v 10 and those works busily in making, and to help, and to make wealsome in the hands of them, and in all glory, full diligently to be performed. 
\p  
\v 11 Then we asked the elder men, saying, Who suffered \sls (or allowed)\sls* you to build this house, and to build \add [or \+sls (to)\+sls* found]\add* these works? 
\p  
\v 12 Therefore forsooth we asked them, \sls (so)\sls* that we might make known to thee the men, and the provosts, \em or reeves\em*; and we asked them the writing of the names of the masters of the work. 
\p  
\v 13 And they answered to us, saying, We be servants of the Lord, that made both heaven and earth \add [or that made heaven and earth]\add*; 
\p  
\v 14 and this house was builded \add [or built]\add* before these many years of \sls (or by)\sls* the king of Israel, that was great, and a full strong king, and it was destroyed \em again\em*\add [or full ended]\add*. 
\p  
\v 15 And for our fathers stirred and sinned against \add [the]\add* God of Israel, he betook them into the hands of Nebuchadnezzar, king of Babylon, king of \sls (the)\sls* Chaldeans; 
\p  
\v 16 and they destroyed and burned up this house, and they brought the people made thrall \add [or captive]\add* into Babylon. 
\p  
\v 17 In the first year reigning Cyrus, king of Babylon, king Cyrus wrote to build up this house; 
\p  
\v 18 and those holy golden vessels and silvern, that Nebuchadnezzar had borne away from the house \em of God\em*, that is in Jerusalem, and had \sls (made)\sls* sacred \sls (or had consecrated)\sls* them in his temple, again king Cyrus brought them forth from the temple that was in Babylon, and they were betaken to Zerubbabel, and to Sanabassar, the under-little-king. 
\p  
\v 19 And it was commanded to them, that they offer these vessels, and they should lay them up in the temple, that was in Jerusalem, and to build up that temple of God in that place. 
\p  
\v 20 Then Sanabassar under-laid the foundaments of the house of the Lord, that is in Jerusalem; and from thence unto now is \sls (still)\sls* abuilding, and hath taken no full ending. 
\p  
\v 21 Now then, O king! if it is deemed of \sls (or by)\sls* thee, that it be perfectly sought \add [or be it perfectly sought]\add* in the king’s libraries of king Cyrus, that be in Babylon; 
\p  
\v 22 and if it were found in the counsel of king Cyrus, \sls (that)\sls* the making of the house of the Lord, that is in Jerusalem, to be begun, and \em if\em* it shall be showed of \sls (or by)\sls* the lord our king, write he to us of these things. 
\p  
\v 23 Then king Darius commanded to be inwardly sought in the libraries; and there was found in Ecbatana, a borough town, that is in the middle region, a place \sls (or a roll)\sls*, in the which were written these things. 
\p  
\v 24 The first year reigning Cyrus king, Cyrus commanded to build up the house of the Lord, that is in Jerusalem, where they burned with continual fire; 
\p  
\v 25 whose height was made of sixty cubits, and the breadth of sixty cubits, squared with three polished stones, and with solar \sls (or throne)\sls* tree of the same region, and with one new solar \sls (or with three rows of polished stones, and one row of new wood from the same region)\sls*; and costs to be given \sls (out)\sls* of the house of king Cyrus; 
\p  
\v 26 and the holy vessels of the house of the Lord, both golden and silvern, that Nebuchadnezzar bare away, that those \add [or they]\add* be put thither into the house, that is in Jerusalem, where they were put. 
\p  
\v 27 And he commanded Sisinnes, the under-little-king of Syria and Phenice \sls (or Phoenicia)\sls*, and Sathrabuzanes, and his fellows, to do \em their\em*\sls (own)\sls* business, and they that were in Syria and Phenice \sls (or Phoenicia)\sls* ordained rulers, that they should abstain them\sls (selves)\sls* from the same place. 
\p  
\v 28 And I also commanded to make \sls (or build)\sls*\em it\em* up all \sls (again)\sls*, and I looked forth, that they help them that be of the captivity of \sls (the)\sls* Jews, unto the time that the temple of the house of the Lord be full\sls (y)\sls* ended \sls (or finished)\sls*; 
\p  
\v 29 and a quantity to be given dili-gently to these men of the travail of the tributes of Celosyria and Phenice \sls (or taxes of Greater Syria and Phoenicia)\sls*, to the sacrifice of the Lord, to Zerubbabel, the prefect, to bulls, and wethers \sls (or rams)\sls*, and to lambs; 
\p  
\v 30 also forsooth both wheat, and salt, wine, and oil, busily by all years, as the priests, that be in Jerusalem, ordained to be fulfilled each day, without any delay; 
\p  
\v 31 \em also\em* that there be offered offer-ings of liquors \sls (or liquid sacrifices)\sls* to the highest God, for the king, and for his children, and pray they for the life of them. 
\p  
\v 32 And be it denounced \sls (or announced)\sls*, that whosoever over-pass anything of these things that be written, either \add [or]\add* despise \sls (them)\sls*, be there taken a tree of their own, and be they hanged \em thereon\em*, and their goods be escheated \sls (or forfeited)\sls* to the king. 
\p  
\v 33 Therefore also the Lord, whose name is inwardly called there, outlaw he each king and folk, that stretch out their hand to offend \add [or to hinder]\add*, or to evil treat that house of the Lord, that is in Jerusalem. 
\p  
\v 34 I, king Darius, have made a decree, to be done as most diligently after these things. 
\c 7  
\cl CHAPTER 7 
\p  
\v 1 Then Sisinnes, the under-little-king of Celosyria and Phenice \sls (or the governor of Greater Syria and Phoe-nicia)\sls*, and Sathrabuzanes, and \em their\em* fellows, obeyed to these things, that were deemed of \sls (or by)\sls* king Darius, 
\p  
\v 2 and stood full diligently into the holy works, working together with the elder men of \sls (the)\sls* Jews, \sls (and)\sls* princes of Syria \sls (or the temple officers)\sls*. 
\p  
\v 3 And the holy works be made wealsome, as the prophets Haggai and Zechariah prophesied. 
\p  
\v 4 And they fulfilled all things, after the behest \sls (or the command)\sls* of the Lord God of Israel, and after the counsel of Cyrus, and of Darius, and of Artaxerxes, king\sls (s)\sls* of Persia. 
\p  
\v 5 And our house is ended \sls (or was finished)\sls*, in the three and twentieth day of the month of March, in the sixth year of king Darius. 
\p  
\v 6 And the sons of Israel, and the priests, and \sls (the)\sls* deacons \add [or Levites]\add*, and others that were of the captivity, the which be set to, did after those things that be written in the book of Moses. 
\p  
\v 7 And they offered into the dedi-cation of the temple of the Lord, an hundred bulls, two hundred wethers \sls (or rams)\sls*, four hundred lambs; 
\p  
\v 8 \sls (and)\sls* twelve kids, for the sins of all Israel, after the number of the twelve lineages of Israel. 
\p  
\v 9 And the priests and \sls (the)\sls* deacons \add [or Levites]\add* stood, clothed \add [or clad]\add* with the stoles, by \em their\em* lineages, upon the works of the Lord God of Israel, after the book of Moses; and \em there were\em* porters \add [or ushers]\add* by all the gates. 
\p  
\v 10 And the sons of Israel did that pask, with them that were of the captivity, in the moon of the first month, the fourteenth \em day\em*, when the priests and \sls (the)\sls* deacons be hallowed. 
\p  
\v 11 And all the sons of \sls (the)\sls* captivity they be not hallowed together, for \sls (or but)\sls* all the Levites be hallowed together. 
\p  
\v 12 And they offered \sls (the)\sls* pask to all the sons of \sls (the)\sls* captivity, and to their brethren \sls (the)\sls* priests, and to themselves. 
\p  
\v 13 And the sons of Israel, the which were of the captivity, all they that had left \sls (or separated)\sls* from all the cursed-nesses of \sls (the)\sls* Gentiles, \em or heathen folk\em*, of the earth, ate, and sought the Lord; 
\p  
\v 14 and they hallowed the feast day of therf loaves, seven days eating in the sight of the Lord; 
\p  
\v 15 for he converted the counsel of the king of Assyria in \sls (or towards)\sls* them, to comfort \sls (or to strengthen)\sls* the hands of them to \sls (or in)\sls* the works of the Lord God of Israel. 
\c 8  
\cl CHAPTER 8 
\p  
\v 1 And after this, while Artaxerxes, king of Persia, reigned, there went to Ezra, \em a man that was\em* the son of Seraiah \sls (or there came Ezra, the son of Seraiah)\sls*, son of Azariah, son of Hilkiah, son of Shallum, 
\p  
\v 2 son of Zadok, son of Ahitub, son of Amariah, son of Azariah, son of Meraioth, son of Zerahiah, son of Uzzi, son of Bukki, son of Abishua, son of Phinehas, son of Eleazar, son of Aaron, the first priest. 
\p  
\v 3 This Ezra went up from Babylon, when he was \sls (a)\sls* scribe, and witty, \sls (or witting, or knowing)\sls* in the law of Moses, the which was given of \sls (or by)\sls* the Lord of Israel, to say \em it\em* and do \em it\em*. 
\p  
\v 4 And the king gave to him glory, that he had found grace in all dignity, and in desire, in the sight of him. 
\p  
\v 5 And there went up with him into Jerusalem \sls (some)\sls* of the sons of Israel, both priests, and deacons, and \sls (the)\sls* holy singers of the temple, and ushers, \sls (or porters)\sls*, and servants of the temple. 
\p  
\v 6 In the seventh year reigning Artaxerxes, in the fifth month, this is the seventh year of the realm \add [or the reign]\add*, going out forsooth from Babylon in the new moon of the fifth month, they came to Jerusalem, after the behests \sls (or commands)\sls* of him, when the prosperity of the way was granted \add [or given]\add* to them of \sls (or by)\sls* that Lord. 
\p  
\v 7 In these things forsooth Ezra wielded great discipline, lest he passed \sls (over)\sls* anything of those things that were of the law of the Lord, and of the behests \sls (or commandments)\sls*, and in teaching all Israel all rightwiseness and doom \sls (or judgements)\sls*. 
\p  
\v 8 They forsooth that write the writings of king Artaxerxes, coming nigh, took writing that \sls (or Now regarding the ordinance, or the decree)\sls*, that came from king Artaxerxes to Ezra, the priest, and reader of the law of the Lord, the ensample of the which thing \em written\em* is set next after \add [or of which thing the example is laid under\+sls (neath)\+sls*]\add*. 
\p  
\v 9 King Artaxerxes to Ezra, the priest, and reader of the law of the Lord, \em sendeth\em* greeting\sls (s)\sls*. 
\p  
\v 10 More benign I deeming also to benefits, commanded to them that desire of the folk of \sls (the)\sls* Jews their own things willfully \sls (or willingly)\sls*, and of the priests, and of \sls (the)\sls* deacons \add [or Levites]\add*, that be in my realm, to fellowship with thee into Jerusalem. 
\p  
\v 11 Then if any covet to go with thee, come they together, and go they forth, as it pleaseth to me, and to my seven friends \sls (the)\sls* counsellors; 
\p  
\v 12 that they visit those things, that be done after \sls (or unto)\sls* Judea and Jerusalem, keeping \em the law\em*, as thou hast in the law of the Lord; 
\p  
\v 13 and bear they gifts to the Lord of Israel, whom I knew, and the friends of Jerusalem, and all the gold and the silver, that were found in the realm of Babylon, \em be it borne\em* to the Lord in Jerusalem, 
\p  
\v 14 with that that is given of \sls (or by)\sls* those folk in \sls (or for)\sls* the temple of the Lord, of \sls (or by)\sls* them that is in Jeru-salem; that this gold be gathered and silver \add [or that be gathered this gold and silver]\add*, to bulls, and wethers \sls (or rams)\sls*, and to lambs, and kids, and that to these be covenable \sls (or suitable)\sls*; 
\p  
\v 15 that they offer hosts to the Lord, upon the altar of the Lord of them, that is in Jerusalem. 
\p  
\v 16 And all things whatever thou wilt do with thy brethren, perform \em it\em* with \sls (the)\sls* gold and silver, for \em thy\em* will, after the behest of the Lord thy God. 
\p  
\v 17 And the sacred holy vessels, the which were given to thee, to \sls (or for)\sls* the works of the Lord’s house, thy God, that is in Jerusalem, 
\p  
\v 18 and other things, whatever will help to \sls (or for)\sls* the works of the temple of thy God, thou shalt give \em it\em*\sls (out)\sls* of the king’s treasury, when thou wilt make the work with thy brethren, with gold and silver; and perform thou all thing\sls (s)\sls* after the will of thy Lord. 
\p  
\v 19 And I, king Artaxerxes, have commanded to \add [the]\add* keepers of the treasures of Syria and of Phenice \sls (or to the treasury officials of Syria and Phoenicia)\sls*, that whatever things Ezra, the priest, and \sls (the)\sls* reader of the law of the Lord, write for, busily \sls (or swiftly)\sls* be it given to him, 
\p  
\v 20 unto an hundred talents of silver, also and of gold \add [or \+sls (in)\+sls* like manner and of gold]\add*; and unto an hundred bushels of wheat, and an hundred vessels of wine, and other things, whatever abound, without taxing. 
\p  
\v 21 All things be done \sls (un)\sls*to the highest God, after the law of God, lest peradventure wrath arise up in the realm of the king, and of his son, and of the sons of him. 
\p  
\v 22 To you forsooth it was said, that to all the priests, and deacons \add [or Levites]\add*, and to \sls (the)\sls* holy singers, and servants of the temple, and to \sls (the)\sls* scribes of this temple, no tribute, nor any other preventing or hindering be borne to \em them\em*, nor have there any man power to against-cast \sls (or impose)\sls* anything to them. 
\p  
\v 23 Thou forsooth, Ezra, after the wisdom of God ordain doomsmen \sls (or judges)\sls* and arbitrators, in all Syria and Phenice \sls (or Phoenicia)\sls*, and teach all \sls (those)\sls* that know \sls (not)\sls* the law of thy God \add [or all that the law of thy God knew \+sls (not)\+sls*, teach]\add*; 
\p  
\v 24 that how many ever \add [over]\add*-pass \sls (or transgress)\sls* the law, they be busily \sls (or swiftly)\sls* punished, or by death, or by torment, or also by mulcting, \em or punishing\em*, of money, or by departing away. 
\p  
\v 25 And Ezra, the scribe, said, Blessed be the Lord God of our fathers, that gave this will \sls (or this desire)\sls* into the heart of the king, to clarify \sls (or to glorify)\sls* his house, that is in Jerusalem; 
\p  
\v 26 and hath worshipped \sls (or honoured)\sls* me in \sls (the)\sls* sight of the king, and of his counsellors, and of his friends, and of his purpled men. 
\p  
\v 27 And I am made steadfast in inwit, after the helping of the Lord our God; and I gathered of Israel men \sls (or I gathered men of Israel)\sls*, that they should go up together with me. 
\p  
\v 28 And these be the provosts, after their countries, and apportional prince-hoods of them, that with me went up from Babylon, in the realm of Artaxerxes. 
\p  
\v 29 Of the sons of Phineas \em was\em* Gershom; of the sons of Ithamar, Gamael; of the sons of David, Attus, the son of Sechenias; 
\p  
\v 30 of the sons of Phoros, Zechariah, and with him be turned again an hundred men and fifty; 
\p  
\v 31 of the sons of Pahath-moab, Eliaonias, \sls (the son of)\sls* Zaraeas, and with him two hundred men and fifty; 
\p  
\v 32 of the sons of Zathoe, Sechenias \sls (the son of)\sls* Jezelus, and with him two hundred men and fifty; of the sons of Adin, Obeth \sls (the son of)\sls* Jonathan, and with him two hundred men and fifty; 
\p  
\v 33 of the sons of Elam, Jessias \sls (the son of)\sls* Gotholias, and with him seventy men; 
\p  
\v 34 of the sons of Sophotias, Zerahiah \sls (the son of)\sls* Michael, and with him fourscore men; 
\p  
\v 35 of the sons of Joab, Abadias \sls (the son of)\sls* Jezelus, and with him two hundred men and twelve; 
\p  
\v 36 of the sons of Bani, Assalimoth \sls (the son of)\sls* Josiphiah, and with him an hundred men and sixty; 
\p  
\v 37 of the sons of Babi, Zechariah \sls (the son of)\sls* Bebai, and with him two hundred men and eight \sls (or twenty-eight men)\sls*; 
\p  
\v 38 of the sons of Astath, Johanan \sls (the son of)\sls* Hacatan, and with him an hundred men and ten; 
\p  
\v 39 of the sons of Adonikam, \em that be\em* the last, and these be the names of them, Eliphalatus, Jeuel, and Samaeas, and with them seventy men; 
\p  
\v 40 (This verse is omitted in the original text.) 
\p  
\v 41 And I gathered them to the flood, that is said Theras and Methati \sls (or And I gathered them together at the river, that is called Theras)\sls*; there we were \sls (for)\sls* three days, and I knew them. 
\p  
\v 42 And of the sons of \sls (the)\sls* priests and of \sls (the)\sls* Levites I found not there. 
\p  
\v 43 And I sent to Eleazar, and to Iduel, and Maasmas, 
\p  
\v 44 and Elnathan, and Samaeas, and Joribus, Nathan, Ennatas, Zechariah, \add [and]\add* Mosollamus, \em the which\em* were leaders and wise men. 
\p  
\v 45 And I said to them that they should come to Doldaeus, \sls (the chief official)\sls*, that was at the place of the treasury. 
\p  
\v 46 And I sent to them, that they should say to Doldaeus, and \sls (to)\sls* his brethren, and to them that were in the treasury, that they should send to us them that should use \sls (the office of the)\sls* priesthood in the house of the Lord our God. 
\p  
\v 47 And they brought to us, after the strong hand of the Lord our God, wise men of the sons of Mahli, son of Levi, son of Israel, Asebebias, and \sls (his)\sls* sons, and \sls (his)\sls* brethren, that were eighteen; 
\p  
\v 48 \sls (and)\sls* Asebias, and Annunus, and Hosaeas, his brother, of the sons of Chanunaeus; and the sons of them, \em were\em* twenty men. 
\p  
\v 49 And of them that served in the temple, the which David and they princes gave \add [or the which David gave, and they princes]\add*, to the working to the Levites, to the temple, of men serving, two hundred and twenty. The names of all be signified in \sls (the)\sls* scriptures \sls (or in the register)\sls*. 
\p  
\v 50 And I vowed there fasting to \sls (the)\sls* young men, in the sight of the Lord, \sls (so)\sls* that I should seek of him a good way to us \sls (or so that I should seek from him a good way for us)\sls*, and \em to \+sls (or for)\+sls* them\em* that were with us, of sons, and beasts, for espies \sls (or safe from ambush)\sls*. 
\p  
\v 51 Forsooth I shamed to ask of the king \sls (for)\sls* footmen and horsemen, in fellowship of grace, of keeping against our adversaries. 
\p  
\v 52 Forsooth we said to the king, For the virtue of the Lord shall be with them, that inwardly seek him in all effect. 
\p  
\v 53 And \sls (so)\sls* again we prayed the Lord our God, after these things, whom also we had benignly; and we be made whole to our God. 
\p  
\v 54 And I parted \sls (or set apart)\sls* of the provosts of the folk, and of the priests of the temple, twelve men, and Sarabias \sls (or yea, Sarabias)\sls*, and Asamias, and ten men with them of their brethren. 
\p  
\v 55 And I weighed \sls (out)\sls* to \sls (or for)\sls* them \sls (the)\sls* silver and \sls (the)\sls* gold, and \sls (the)\sls* priests’ vessels, of the house of the Lord our God, the which the king had given, and his counsellors, and princes, and all Israel. 
\p  
\v 56 And when I had peised \sls (or weighed)\sls*\em it\em*\sls (out)\sls*, I took an hundred talents of silver and fifty, and silvern vessels of an hundred talents, and of gold an hundred talents, 
\p  
\v 57 and of golden vessels sevenscore, and twelve brazen vessels of good shining metal, yielding the likeness of gold. 
\p  
\v 58 And I said to them, Both ye be holy to the Lord, and the vessels be holy, and the gold and the silver is of the avow to the Lord God of our fathers. 
\p  
\v 59 Wake ye, and keep \em it\em*, till the time that ye take \em it\em* of \sls (or to)\sls* the provosts of the people, and of the priests, and of the deacons, and of \sls (the)\sls* princes of the cities of Israel, and Jerusalem \add [or in Jerusalem]\add*, in the privy chamber of the house of our God. 
\p  
\v 60 And these priests and deacons \add [or Levites]\add*, that took \sls (the)\sls* gold and silver, and \sls (the)\sls* vessels, that were in Jerusalem, they brought \em those\em* into the temple of the Lord. 
\p  
\v 61 And we moved forth from the flood of Theras, the twelfth day of the first month, till that we went into Jerusalem. 
\p  
\v 62 And when the third day was done, the fourth day forsooth the peised gold and silver was betaken into the house of the Lord our God, to Marmathi, the son of Uri, the priest; 
\p  
\v 63 and with him was Eleazar, the son of Phinehas; and there were with them Jozabdus, the son of Jeshua, and Moeth, and Sabannus, the son of a deacon \sls (or and Moeth, the son of Sabannus, Levites)\sls*; all things \sls (were delivered to them)\sls* at number and weight. 
\p  
\v 64 And the weight of them is written \sls (up)\sls* in the same hour. 
\p  
\v 65 Those forsooth, that came from the captivity, offered sacrifice of \sls (or unto)\sls* the Lord of Israel, twelve bulls for all Israel, fourscore wethers and six \sls (or eighty-six rams)\sls*, 
\p  
\v 66 two and seventy lambs, twelve goats for sin, and twelve kine for health; all into the sacrifice of the Lord. 
\p  
\v 67 And again they read the behests of the king to the king’s dispensers, and to the little-under-kings \sls (or to the under-little-kings)\sls* of Celosyria, and of Phenice; and they worshipped the folk and the temple of the Lord. 
\p  
\v 68 And after these things were ended, they came to me, saying, 
\p  
\v 69 The kindred of Israel, and the princes, and the priests, and Levites \sls (or deacons)\sls*, and alien folks, and \sls (the)\sls* nations of the land, have not parted away \add [or severed]\add* their uncleannesses from the Canaanites, and Hittites, and from \sls (the)\sls* Perizzites, and Jebusites, and from the Moabites, and Egyptians, and Idumeans \sls (or Edomites)\sls*; 
\p  
\v 70 forsooth they were joined to the daughters of them, both they and their sons; and the holy seed was \add [or is]\add* mingled \sls (or mixed)\sls* together with the heathen folk of the land; and the provosts and master judges were partners of this wickedness, from the beginning of that realm. 
\p  
\v 71 And anon \sls (or at once)\sls* as I heard these things, I cut \em my\em* clothes, and the hallowed \add [or the sacred]\add* coat, and I tore the hairs of mine head, and the beard, \em and\em* I sat sorrowing, and dreary. 
\p  
\v 72 And there came to me then as many as ever were moved in \sls (or by)\sls* the word of the Lord God of Israel, wailing me \add [or me wailing]\add* upon this wickedness \sls (or while I wailed over this iniquity)\sls*; and I sat sorrowful unto the eventide sacrifice. 
\p  
\v 73 And \em then\em* I rising from fasting, having my clothes cut, kneeled much \add [or much kneeling]\add*, and stretching out \em mine\em* hands to the Lord, 
\p  
\v 74 I said, Lord, I am confounded \sls (or confused)\sls*, and I am adread before thy face. 
\p  
\v 75 Forsooth our sins be multiplied upon our heads, and our wickednesses be enhanced \sls (or be exalted or raised up)\sls* unto heaven; 
\p  
\v 76 for from the time of our fathers we have been in great sin unto this day. 
\p  
\v 77 And for our own sins, and \em for the sins\em* of our fathers we be taken, with our brethren, and with our priests, and with kings of the land, into sword, and captivity, and into prey, with confusion, unto the day that is now. 
\p  
\v 78 And now how much is \em it\em*, that the mercy of thee, Lord God, falleth to us; leave thou to us a root and a name, into the place of thine hallowing \sls (or in the place of thy sanctuary)\sls*, 
\p  
\v 79 to uncover \sls (or to discover)\sls* our giver of light in the house of the Lord our God, to give to us meat in the time of our servage \sls (or to give us food in the time of our servitude)\sls*. 
\p  
\v 80 And when we served \sls (in bondage)\sls*, we were not forsaken of \sls (or by)\sls* the Lord our God; but he set us in grace, putting to us kings of Persia to give \em us\em* meat \sls (or food)\sls*, 
\p  
\v 81 and to clarify \sls (or to glorify)\sls* the temple of the Lord our God, and to build \sls (up)\sls* the deserts \sls (or the ruins)\sls* of Zion, and to give to us stableness in Judea and in Jerusalem. 
\p  
\v 82 And now, Lord, what say we, having these things? We have over-passed thy behests \sls (or have transgress-ed thy commandments)\sls*, the which thou give \add [or thou gave]\add* into the hands of thy children \sls (or which thou gavest by the hands of thy servants)\sls*, \sls (the)\sls* prophets, that said, 
\p  
\v 83 Forsooth the land, in\sls (to)\sls* which ye have entered, to wield the heritage of it, is a defouled \sls (or a defiled)\sls* land with the filths of \add [the]\add* heathen men of the land, and the uncleannesses of them have full-filled all \sls (of)\sls* it \add [or have full-filled it all]\add* in \sls (or with)\sls* his uncleanness. 
\p  
\v 84 And now \em therefore\em* ye shall not join your daughters to their sons, and their daughters ye shall not take to yours sons; 
\p  
\v 85 and ye shall not seek to have peace with them \sls (for)\sls* all time, \sls (so)\sls* that coming above ye eat the best things of the land, and \sls (so)\sls* that ye deal the heritage to your sons, ever\sls (more)\sls*. 
\p  
\v 86 And those things that fall to us, be they all done for our shrewd \sls (or depraved)\sls* works, and our great sins. 
\p  
\v 87 And thou hast given to us such a root, and again we be turned again to over-pass \sls (or transgress)\sls* thy lawful things, \sls (so)\sls* that the uncleannesses of the heathen folk of this land were mingled. 
\p  
\v 88 Whether thou shalt not wrath to us, to lose \sls (or to destroy)\sls* us, for till the root be forsaken, and our seed? 
\p  
\v 89 Lord God of Israel, thou art sooth-fast; forsooth the root is forsaken, unto the day that is now. 
\p  
\v 90 Lo! now we be in thy sight in our wickednesses; forsooth it is not yet to stand before thee in these things. 
\p  
\v 91 And when Ezra honouring \sls (or worshipping)\sls* acknowledged, weeping, he fell down to the earth before the temple, there be gathered before him a full great multitude of Jerusalem \add [or be gathered before him of Jerusalem a full great company or crowd]\add*, men, and women, and young men, and young women; forsooth the weeping was great in that multitude. 
\p  
\v 92 And when Jechonias, the son of Jeel, of the sons of Israel, had cried, Ezra said, We have sinned against the Lord \sls (or And then Jechonias, the son of Jeel, one of the sons of Israel, cried out, and said, O Ezra, we have sinned against the Lord)\sls*, \em for\em* that we have set with us into matrimony heathen women, of the Gentiles of the land. 
\p  
\v 93 And now whosoever is over all Israel in these things, be there to us an oath of \sls (or to)\sls* the Lord, to put away all our wives, that be, with their sons, of the heathen folk; 
\p  
\v 94 as it is deemed to \sls (or by)\sls* thee of the greater men, after the law of the Lord. 
\p  
\v 95 Arise \em now\em* up, and show \add [out]\add*\em thy will\em*; forsooth to thee abideth this need, and we be with thee; do manly. 
\p  
\v 96 And Ezra arising up, made the princes of \sls (the)\sls* priests, and the deacons \add [or the Levites]\add*, and \sls (or of)\sls* all Israel, to swear to do after all these things; and they swore. 
\c 9  
\cl CHAPTER 9 
\p  
\v 1 And Ezra rising up from the fore-porch \sls (or the courtyard)\sls* of the temple, went into the cell \sls (or the room)\sls* of Johanan, the son of Eliasibus. 
\p  
\v 2 And he harboured there, tasted no bread, nor drank water, for the wickednesses of the multitude. 
\p  
\v 3 And there was made a preaching in all Judea and in Jerusalem, to all that were of the captivity \sls (that they should be)\sls* gathered \sls (together)\sls* in Jerusalem, 
\p  
\v 4 \sls (And)\sls* Whosoever again-cometh not to the second or the third day, after the doom of the elder men sitting, his faculties shall be taken away, and \sls (that)\sls* he be deemed alien \sls (or stranger, or cast out)\sls* from the multitude of the captivity. 
\p  
\v 5 And all, that were of the lineage\sls (s)\sls* of Judah and Benjamin, were gathered together, three days \sls (later)\sls* in Jerusalem; this is the ninth month, the twentieth day of the month. 
\p  
\v 6 And all the multitude sat in the floor \sls (or the open space)\sls* of the temple, trembling for winter \em then\em* being. 
\p  
\v 7 \em And\em* Ezra rising up, said to Israel, Ye have done wickedly, setting to you into matrimony heathen wives, \sls (so)\sls* that ye add to the sins of Israel. 
\p  
\v 8 And now give ye to the Lord God of our fathers confession, and great worthiness; 
\p  
\v 9 and perform ye his will, and goeth away from the heathen folk of the land, and from heathen wives. 
\p  
\v 10 And all the multitude cried, and they said with a great \sls (or a loud)\sls* voice, We shall do, as thou hast said. 
\p  
\v 11 But for the multitude is great, and the time is winter, and we may not stand unholpen, \add [or unhelped]\add*, \sls (or without help)\sls*, and this work is not to \sls (or for)\sls* us of one day, nor of two; \sls (for)\sls* much we have sinned in these things; 
\p  
\v 12 \em therefore\em* stand the provosts of the multitude, and all that dwell with us, and how many ever have with them heathen wives; 
\p  
\v 13 and stand they nigh in the time that is taken \add [or in the accept\+sls (able)\+sls* time of \+sls (or in)\+sls* all place\+sls (s)\+sls*]\add*, priests, and doomsmen, till that they lose \sls (or turn away)\sls* the wrath of the Lord, of this need \sls (or over this matter)\sls*. 
\p  
\v 14 Jonathan forsooth, the son of Azael, and Hezekiah, \sls (the son of)\sls* Thocanus, took after these things, and Mosollamus, and Levi, and Sabba-taeus wrought together with them. 
\p  
\v 15 And all that were of the captivity stood \em there\em*, after all these things. 
\p  
\v 16 And Ezra, \sls (the)\sls* priest, chose to him\sls (self)\sls* men, \sls (the)\sls* great princes, of the fathers of them, after the names; and they sat together, in the new moon of the tenth month, to examine this need \sls (or this matter)\sls*. 
\p  
\v 17 And it is determined of the men, that had heathen wives, unto the new moons of the first month. 
\p  
\v 18 And there be found mingled \sls (or mixed)\sls* among of the priests, that had heathen wives; 
\p  
\v 19 of the sons of Jesus, \sls (or Jeshua, or Joshua)\sls*, the son of Josedek, and of his brethren, Mathelas, and Eleazar, and Joribus, and Joadanus. 
\p  
\v 20 And they laid \sls (or put up)\sls*\em their\em* hands, that they should \sls (or would)\sls* put away their wives, and for to sacrifice a ram, into prayer for their ignorance. 
\p  
\v 21 And of the sons of Emmer, Ananias, and Zabdaeus, and Manes, and Samaeus, and Jereel, \sls (and)\sls* Azarias; 
\p  
\v 22 and of the sons of Phaesus, Elionas, Massias, Ishmael, and Nathanael, and Okidelus, and Saloas. 
\p  
\v 23 And of the deacons \add [or the Levites]\add*, Jozabadus, and Semis, and Colius, who was called Calitas, and Phathaeus, and Judas, and Jonas. 
\p  
\v 24 And of the hallowed \add [or the sacred]\add* singers, Eliasibus, \sls (and)\sls* Bacchurus. 
\p  
\v 25 And of the ushers, Sallumus, and Tolbanes. \sls (And of the porters, Shallum, and Telem.)\sls* 
\p  
\v 26 And of Israel, of the sons of Phoros, Jermas, and Jeddias, and Melchias, and Maelus, and Eleazar, and Asibias, and Bannaeas. 
\p  
\v 27 And of the sons of Ela, Matthanias, and Zechariah, \sls (and)\sls* Jezrielus, and Jeremoth, and Aedias. 
\p  
\v 28 And of the sons of Zamoth, Eliadas, and Eliasimus, and Othonias, and Jarimoth, and Sabathus, and Zardaeus. 
\p  
\v 29 And of the sons of Bebai, Johannes, and Ananias, and Ozabadus, and Emathis. 
\p  
\v 30 And of the sons of Mani, Olamus, and Mamuchus, and Jedaeus, and Jasubus, and Asaelus, and Jeremoth. 
\p  
\v 31 And of the sons of Addi, Naathus, and Moossias, and Laccunus, and Naidus, Matthanias, and Sesthel, and Balnuus, and Manasseas. 
\p  
\v 32 And of the sons of Annas, Elionas, and Asaeas, and Melchias, and Sabbaeus, and Simon Chosamaeus. 
\p  
\v 33 And of the sons of Asom, Altan-naeus, Mattathias, and Bannaeus, and Eliphalat, and Manasseh, and Shimei. 
\p  
\v 34 And of the sons of Bani, Jeremiah, and Momdis, and Ismaerus, and Juel, and Mandae, and Paedias, and Anos, Carabasion, and Enasibus, and Mamni-tanaemus, and Eliasis, and Bannus, and Eliali, and Somis, and Selemias, and Nathaniah; and of the sons of Ezora, Sessis, and Ezril, and Azael, and Samatus, and Zambris, and Josephus. 
\p  
\v 35 And of the sons of Nooma, Mazitias, and Zabadaeas, and Edaes, and Juel, \sls (and)\sls* Banaeas. 
\p  
\v 36 All \sls (of)\sls* these \sls (had)\sls* joined to them-\sls (selves)\sls* heathen wives, and \sls (now)\sls* left them \sls (or let them go)\sls*, with \em their\em* sons. 
\p  
\v 37 And \sls (the)\sls* priests, and deacons, and they that were of Israel, dwelled in Jerusalem in an one region \sls (or dwelled in Jerusalem, and its vicinity)\sls*, \sls (in)\sls* the new moon of the seventh month; and the sons of Israel were in their abidings. 
\p  
\v 38 And all the multitude gathered together in the floor \sls (or in the open space)\sls*, that is from the east of the hallowed \add [or the sacred]\add* gate. 
\p  
\v 39 And they said to Ezra, \sls (the)\sls* bishop and reader, that he should bring forth the law of Moses, that was given of \sls (or by)\sls* the Lord God of Israel. 
\p  
\v 40 And Ezra, the bishop, brought forth the law to all the multitude of them, from man unto woman, and to all the priests, to hear the law, in the new moon of the seventh month. 
\p  
\v 41 And he read in the floor \sls (or the open space)\sls*, that is before the holy gate of the temple, from the first light \em of the day\em* unto even\sls (ing)\sls*, before men and women; and all they gave wit, \sls (or thought, or understanding)\sls* to the law. 
\p  
\v 42 And Ezra, the priest, and reader of the law, stood \add [up]\add* upon the treen \sls (or the wooden)\sls* chair, that was made \em therefore\em*. 
\p  
\v 43 And there stood with him Mattathias, and Sammus, and Ananias, Azariah, Uriah, Hezekiah, and Baal-samus, at the right side; 
\p  
\v 44 and at the left side, Phaldaeus, Mishael, Melchias, Lothasubus, Nabariah, and Zechariah. 
\p  
\v 45 And Ezra took a book before all the multitude; forsooth he sat before in worship \sls (or in honour)\sls*, in the sight of all. 
\p  
\v 46 And when he had assoiled the law \sls (or had opened, or had expounded upon, the law)\sls*, all they stood upright. And Ezra blessed the Lord God, alder-Highest God of \sls (the)\sls* Sabbath, Almighty or all mighty. 
\p  
\v 47 And all the people answered, Amen. And again they raised up \em their\em* hands, and falling down unto the earth, they honoured \sls (or worshipped)\sls* the Lord. 
\p  
\v 48 And Ezra commanded, that these should teach the law, Jesus, \sls (or Jeshua, or Joshua)\sls*, and Annus, and Sarabias, and Jadinus, and Jacubus, and Sabba-taeas, and Autaeas, and Maeannas, and Calitas, and Azarias, and Jozab-dus, and Ananias, and Phiathas, \sls (the)\sls* deacons \add [or Levites]\add*. The which taught the law of the Lord, and in \sls (or to)\sls* the multitude they read the law of the Lord; and each by himself, that under-stood the lesson, told \em it\em* before them. 
\p  
\v 49 And Attharates said to Ezra \sls (or And the governor said to Ezra)\sls*, the bishop and reader, and to the Levites that taught the multitude, saying, 
\p  
\v 50 This day is holy to the Lord. And all they wept, when they had heard the law. 
\p  
\v 51 And Ezra said, Ye therefore, after ye be gone atwain, eateth all most fat things, and drinketh all most sweet, and send ye gifts to them that have not; 
\p  
\v 52 forsooth this day of the Lord is holy; and be ye not sorry, the Lord forsooth shall clarify us \sls (or for the Lord shall glorify us)\sls*. 
\p  
\v 53 And the deacons \add [or the Levites]\add* denounced \sls (or announced)\sls*, \em or showed\em*, openly to all men, saying, This day is holy; will ye not \sls (to)\sls* be sorry \sls (or resolve not to be sorrowful)\sls*. 
\p  
\v 54 And then all they went away, to eat, and to drink, and to have plenty of meat \sls (or food)\sls*, and to give gifts to them that have not, whereof to eat plenteously. 
\p  
\v 55 Greatly forsooth they be enhanced in the words, with the which they be taught. And all they were gathered into Jerusalem, to make solemn the gladness, after the testament of the Lord God of Israel. 